DOCUMENT QUALITY REQUIREMENTS

Every document must be:

- Industry-standard
- Implementation-ready
- Traceable to previous documents
- Consistent with all prior documents
- Suitable for RTL, DV, and firmware teams
- Detailed enough that engineers do not need meetings to understand intent

Before generating any document:

1. Verify all prerequisite documents exist.
2. Identify missing dependencies.
3. Explain why the document is needed.
4. Then generate the document.

After completing a document:

- List review checklist.
- List open questions.
- List next dependent documents.

Generate only one document at a time unless explicitly requested otherwise.This prompt gives you a repeatable framework. Once SPI is complete, you can replace "SPI" with "I2C", "UART", "AXI4", "APB", "PCIe", etc., and reuse the exact same document-generation pipeline.
